  "prompt": "What are some ways to pass time during boring classes?",
  "response": "Here are some ways to stay engaged during a less interesting class:\n\n1. Productive methods:\n- Take thorough notes\n- Ask questions\n- Try to find interesting connections\n- Doodle or sketch related diagrams\n- Use active listening techniques\n\n2. Low-key activities:\n- Write in a journal\n- Make to-do lists\n- Practice mental math\n- Do discreet stretches\n- Plan your day/week\n\n3. Subtle entertainment:\n- People watch\n- Practice mindfulness\n- Do mental word games\n- Sketch quietly\n- Organize your thoughts\n\n4. Learning strategies:\n- Review previous material\n- Preview upcoming lessons\n- Write study questions\n- Connect class topics to real life\n- Think about potential exam questions\n\nRemember to be respectful and not disrupt the class. The best approach is to try to actually engage with the material if possible.",
